{"TopicId":127000,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Virgin Galactic, Branson\u0026#039;s space venture","CreatedByName":"PB666","CreatedById":107380,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-04T15:04:53Z","PageNum":22,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-23T02:01:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAmazon lost money for what, 15 years? And now how profitable are they?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis \u0022simple math\u0022 is probably *too* simple. I\u0027m not saying I expect them to be making money next quarter or anything, and they may never make money, but developing a flight vehicle is very expensive. That doesn\u0027t mean you keep spending money at that rate after it has been developed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-23T02:35:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224095530\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022127000\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221645581662\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n51 minutes ago, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAmazon lost money for what, 15 years? And now how profitable are they?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis \u0022simple math\u0022 is probably *too* simple. I\u0027m not saying I expect them to be making money next quarter or anything, and they may never make money, but developing a flight vehicle is very expensive. That doesn\u0027t mean you keep spending money at that rate after it has been developed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAbsolutely true, but the use case here is the consumer base of people who can spend almost a half a million bucks on a 12 min ride. Seems unlikely they can book 730 seats a year\u2014to break even\u2014in market can also choose BO. Then do it for years.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt the end of the 15 years of loss, Amazon had a rather huge market in front of them\u2026 not sure that\u2019s true of space tourism at the suborbital for $$$$$$$$$$ level\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-02-23T02:52:51Z\u0022 title=\u002202/23/2022 02:52  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 23, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by tater\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-23T02:53:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it could turn into a mass market, then yeah, all bets are off.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-23T03:44:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20211022005196/en/Global-Sub-Orbital-Space-Tourism-Market-Analysis-and-Research-Report-2021-2031---ResearchAndMarkets.com\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20211022005196/en/Global-Sub-Orbital-Space-Tourism-Market-Analysis-and-Research-Report-2021-2031---ResearchAndMarkets.com\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe global sub-orbital space tourism market is estimated to reach $396.6 million in 2031, at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 24.46% during the forecast period 2021-2031.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAssuming this is correct, and Virgin still burns only $80M/quarter (which is with 1 spaceship, and 1 in dev, vs supposedly 6\u002B later), then Virgin would need to secure ~80% of the market to break even.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-05-05T21:03:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7118336972\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SciGuySpace/status/1522310248303890434\u0022 style=\u0022height:426px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-05-13T15:21:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4644517035\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/Virgin/status/1524479958583853061\u0022 style=\u0022height:609px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-05-13T15:52:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224131444\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022127000\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221652455298\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n27 minutes ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9433343664\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/Virgin/status/1524479958583853061\u0022 style=\u0022height:610px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m pretty sure I mentioned this before, but they are clearly making use of the hard point built on every 747 wing that was originally intended as a way to ferry around a 5th engine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-05-13T17:53:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224131450\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022127000\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221652457120\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m pretty sure I mentioned this before, but they are clearly making use of the hard point built on every 747 wing that was originally intended as a way to ferry around a 5th engine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLearn something new every day:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022SaE8r.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002260.67\u0022 height=\u0022401\u0022 width=\u0022661\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.stack.imgur.com/SaE8r.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-05-19T19:45:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6926038785\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/richardbranson/status/1526185415362977792\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-29T15:39:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2727560240\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/VirginOrbit/status/1542169910268280832\u0022 style=\u0022height:913px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n13 hours:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/O662GsLrdhc?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Virgin Orbit\u2019s Straight Up Mission\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-30T05:20:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nForgot to check stream... apparently scrubbed tonight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-02T04:30:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/O662GsLrdhc?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Virgin Orbit\u2019s Straight Up Mission\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-02T05:23:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMusic is on, takeoff in ~20 m\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9532373778\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/VirginOrbit/status/1543099739100815360\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDrop is about an hour after takeoff. Yeesh. 1:20 of coverage? Hard pass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-02T13:47:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWorked, apparently.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-07T04:11:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3248887227\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/sciguyspace/status/1544802988690210818\u0022 style=\u0022height:631px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-07T04:36:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounding like VMS Eve is showing her age\u2026\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if a mothership capable of flying higher could eke out enough performance gain to actually get SS3 to 100km\u2026.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot that they said anything about a higher release point, just spitballing\u2026\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-04T21:51:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed230456597\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/jeff_foust/status/1555303593649082368\u0022 style=\u0022height:411px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2911560962\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/jeff_foust/status/1555307540220723201\u0022 style=\u0022height:459px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-16T21:16:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2209484454\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/VirginOrbit/status/1603860243632427008\u0022 style=\u0022height:773px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-05T19:52:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6536579489\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/uk_caa/status/1611032908248092673\u0022 style=\u0022height:634px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNET Jan 9\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beccab","CreatedById":208000,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-05T20:07:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst ever orbital launch from Europe! I\u0027m still astonished that over 75 years after Sputnik it still hasn\u0027t happened yet\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-09T18:12:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2 hours:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://youtu.be/5Co18HcyqHk\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://youtu.be/5Co18HcyqHk\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(embeds on NSF, says it won\u0027t here)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-09T22:04:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTaking off right now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-09T22:21:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot dropping for like 50 minutes. Yawn\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GuessingEveryDay","CreatedById":203507,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-09T23:03:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow long have they had the interpreters there? Currently one of my favorite companies as they are the only ones with interpreters for the deaf.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-09T23:09:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224217393\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022127000\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221673305426\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022203507\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GuessingEveryDay\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, GuessingEveryDay said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow long have they had the interpreters there? Currently one of my favorite companies as they are the only ones with interpreters for the deaf.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow, you could answer a question I thought of when I noticed that: Is having an interpreter actually easier to follow than closed captions?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI watch plenty of shows in other languages with subtitles, and while it sometimes distracts from the visuals, I\u0027d assume\u2014as someone who doesn\u0027t sign\u2014that watching a person might take even more focus... but of course I am clueless, and have no experience.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}